// Aliased import alias resolves in type-decl MEMBER positions used INSIDE a
// depth-2 package module (#2202) -- the regression guard for the per-module
// alias-key agreement between the checker and HIR member-lowering.
//
// `hew::aliasmember` (dotted path `hew.aliasmember`, depth >= 2) does
// `import hew::aliassrc::{ Payload as Tag }` and uses `Tag` as a record field
// (`DeepBoxed { item: Tag }`) and an enum-variant payload (`DeepWrap::Has(Tag)`).
// Its `member_score()` constructs and reads both.
//
// The checker keys the per-module alias map by the importer's FULL dotted path
// (`hew.aliasmember`); HIR member-lowering must use the SAME key. If HIR keyed
// by the short last segment (`aliasmember`), the depth-2 importer's aliased
// members would be missed during lowering and freeze as the bare `Tag`, then
// fail closed at the MIR boundary (`unknown type Tag`). A depth-1 importer
// cannot catch this -- short and full keys coincide at the root.
//
// `member_score()` = DeepBoxed.item.code (20) + DeepWrap::Has payload (13) = 33.
//
// Harness verb: hew run
// Expected: 33 -- both depth-2 member positions resolved end-to-end.
import hew::aliasmember;

fn main() {
    println(aliasmember.member_score());
}
